CNCP v1 22985
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#1800: v-model on a custom element (select v-model)",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:28:19.643180+00:00",
  "text": "v-model on a custom element (select v-model)\n\n### Version\r\n3.0.0-rc.5\r\n\r\n### Reproduction link\r\n[https://github.com/vuejs/vue-next/blob/master/packages/compiler-dom/src/transforms/vModel.ts#L93](https://github.com/vuejs/vue-next/blob/master/packages/compiler-dom/src/transforms/vModel.ts#L93)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n- try to us a web component with the \"select api\"\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\nBe able to specify type=select for a web component ?\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\nV_MODEL_SELECT is hard coded to the select tag so we cannot we this directive with a custom element.\r\n\r\n---\r\nTo complete this one : https://github.com/vuejs/vue-next/issues/1699\r\n\r\nIt is a custom component so yes we can provide api compatible with other(s) directive(s) (combo text   lazy for example) but I think that it is a valuable use case.\r\nWhat do you think ?\r\n\r\nOtherwise it is working great with custom elements using others directives, thanks !\r\n\r\n<!-- generated by vue-issues. DO NOT REMOVE -->",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":sparkles: feature request",
    "scope: compiler"
  ],
